        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>157 Allen Str  New&#45;York April 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1885<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I beg to inform you that I will act<lb/> according to your kind <sic>advise</sic> and will<lb/> write to Dr Bettelheim&#44; but I shall not<lb/> stay here so long waiting for his answer<lb/> as I have already taken a <sic>passege</sic><lb/> ticket for Paris. I shall only wait<lb/> for your kind recommendation to Mr.<lb/> Veneziani&#91;&#63;&#93; I am sorry for having<lb/> given you <sic>an</sic> still giving  you so much<lb/> trouble. It appears that the reader of<lb/> my hebrew letter did not call your<lb/> attention to the conclusion of my<lb/> letter where I said &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> &#40;You should be kind enough to send me<lb/> the known letter to the known gentleman.&#41;<lb/> I meant the mentioned letter of recommen&#45;<lb/>dation to Mr Veni&#58; what I <sic>beged</sic> of you<lb/> before leaving Philadelphia<lb/></p>
            <p>P. t. o.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I beg once more to pardon me<lb/> for the trouble I am giving to you<lb/> Please send me the few lines<lb/> to Mr. Veneziani in Paris<lb/> to the <sic>Adress</sic> of Mr. Leszezynski here<lb/> at your earliest <sic>conveniance</sic><lb/></p>
            <p>With heartfelt thanks for your<lb/> former bestowed on me favors<lb/> and with due regard to you <lb/> and yours<lb/></p>
            <p>I remain Rev&#58; Sir<lb/>
                your most <sic>obeidient</sic> servant<lb/>
                Hirsch Krotowsky<lb/>
                I shall stay here till Monday next.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
                <p>H. Krotowski<lb/>
                care of A Leszezynski<lb/>
                112 Rivington Str<lb/>
                New York<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
